<subSubSection pageId="170" pageNumber="773" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="170.[1978,2572,1675,2099]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1978,2134,1675,1704]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1911" box="[2156,2398,1675,1704]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kempi">Thamnomys kempi</taxonomicName>
majorHatt, 1934, 
<materialsCitation pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
<materialsCitation pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
Lukumi, north slope Mt. Karisimbi, Kivu volcanoes, 12,000 ft (= 3600 m), Nord-Kivu Province, E DR Congo. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hatt" authorityYear="1934" box="[1983,2235,1829,1863]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">Thamnomys major</taxonomicName>
, although sometimes included in 7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1911" box="[2198,2271,1873,1902]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kempi">kempi</taxonomicName>
, 1s apparently distinguishable from latter by its much larger size and the more saturated color of its belly y. Monotypic op.
</materialsCitation>
<subSubSection pageId="170" pageNumber="773" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" targetBox="[2218,2222,2626,2651]" targetPageId="170">
<paragraph blockId="170.[1978,2572,1675,2099]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1979,2155,2026,2060]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from type locality in extreme E DR Congo.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="170" pageNumber="773" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="170.[1366,2571,2105,2651]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1367,1614,2105,2139]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 156 mm, tail 201 mm, hindfoot 31 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Large arboreal rodent with bright orange-rufous fur and long tail. Hatt’s Thicket Rat is very like 7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1911" box="[1957,2030,2188,2217]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kempi">kempi</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs only in its larger size and its belly color, which is saturated buffy suffused with gray(whitish gray and sometimes with buff tinge in 7. kempr).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="170" pageNumber="773" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="170.[1366,2571,2105,2651]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1367,1478,2306,2335]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">Habitat.</emphasis>
Holotype was collected in 
<taxonomicName box="[1853,2122,2306,2335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Hagenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Rosaceae">Hagenia (Rosaceae)</taxonomicName>
forest at high altitude (3600 m) on Mount Karisimbi, in Albertine Rift.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1367,1867,2381,2415]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="170.[1366,2571,2105,2651]" box="[1367,1867,2381,2415]" pageId="170" pageNumber="773">
